{#
/**
 * @file
 * Template for an accessible card component.
 *
 * Generated to verify drupal-a11y-dom skill rules:
 * - No redundant ARIA roles on native semantic elements.
 * - Decorative SVG icon uses aria-hidden="true" (visible to sighted users,
 *   hidden from AT) — correct because the adjacent text label is present.
 * - aria-hidden="true" is NOT placed on a focusable element.
 * - Visually-hidden screen-reader suffix uses Drupal's core .visually-hidden
 *   class, not a hand-rolled equivalent.
 * - SVG uses fill="currentColor" so it inherits text colour in dark mode
 *   and forced-colours mode.
 * - "Read more" link has a 24×24 CSS px minimum hit area (enforced in CSS;
 *   documented here for reviewers).
 * - No role="button" on a <button>, no role="navigation" on a <nav>, etc.
 *
 * Available variables:
 *   - title: The card heading text (string, already translated by preprocess).
 *   - url: The URL object / string for the "Read more" link.
 *   - attributes: HTML attributes for the outer <article> element.
 *   - heading_level: The heading level to render (defaults to 3).
 */
#}
{%
  set heading_level = heading_level|default(3)
%}

{#
  Use <article> for a self-contained card; no role="article" needed
  because <article> carries its own implicit ARIA role.
  Drupal's `attributes` object merges preprocess-supplied classes safely.
#}
<article{{ attributes.addClass('card') }}>

  <{{ 'h' ~ heading_level }} class="card__title">
    {{ title }}
  </{{ 'h' ~ heading_level }}>

  <div class="card__footer">
    {#
      The SVG is purely decorative here: the adjacent link text already
      describes the destination. aria-hidden="true" hides it from AT.

      Rules applied (drupal-a11y-dom):
      • aria-hidden="true" on an inert SVG is correct when sighted users
        see it but it would be confusing/duplicate for screen-reader users.
      • Never put aria-hidden="true" on a focusable element — the <svg>
        has no tabindex and is not interactive, so this is safe.
      • fill="currentColor" so the icon inherits active text colour in
        dark mode and forced-colours/High Contrast mode.
    #}
    <a href="{{ url }}" class="card__link">
      <svg
        class="card__icon"
        aria-hidden="true"
        focusable="false"
        width="16"
        height="16"
        viewBox="0 0 16 16"
        fill="currentColor"
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
      >
        {# Simple right-arrow path — decorative only. #}
        <path d="M6 3l5 5-5 5V3z"/>
      </svg>

      {#
        Visible link text. By itself "Read more" is ambiguous for AT users
        scanning a list of cards, so a visually-hidden suffix adds context.

        drupal-a11y-dom rule: use Drupal's core .visually-hidden class.
        Do NOT redefine it locally; core ships it. Do NOT use display:none
        or visibility:hidden here — those would hide the text from AT too.
      #}
      <span class="card__link-visible">{{ 'Read more'|t }}</span>
      <span class="visually-hidden">{{ 'about %title'|t({'%title': title}) }}</span>
    </a>
  </div>

</article>
